00:56.473 --> 00:58.692
Once upon a time...
很久以前...

00:59.810 --> 01:02.029
not so long ago...
其实也不算太久...

02:23.185 --> 02:31.087
奇异恐惧

02:32.585 --> 02:34.287
东伦敦 哈克尼区

03:04.685 --> 03:06.687
Ah!
啊!

03:13.902 --> 03:16.405
This is the story of me.
这就是我的故事

03:16.613 --> 03:18.240
Jack.
我叫杰克

03:19.574 --> 03:23.829
There I am, absolutely shitting it.
我就是这么一个爱死了逃避的人

03:27.541 --> 03:30.841
I'd been carrying a carving knife with me for three weeks
由于内心有一种害怕被谋杀的荒谬恐惧

03:31.044 --> 03:34.344
due to an irrational fear of being murdered.
这三个礼拜以来我都随身带着雕刻刀

03:37.426 --> 03:39.599
I couldn't sleep at night.
而且夜不能寐

03:39.803 --> 03:43.307
As soon as I got into bed, I started seeing killers.
我一上床 就看见杀手来了

03:52.190 --> 03:55.239
These killers were the subject of a series of plays
这些杀手是我曾经为电视台写的一部剧

03:55.444 --> 03:59.290
I had been writing for television.
里面的主题人物

03:59.531 --> 04:02.125
The nature of the project necessitated research
这个节目的本质就是研究

04:02.325 --> 04:04.953
into heinous Victorian criminals.
维多利亚女王时期那些穷凶极恶的犯人

04:05.162 --> 04:09.133
And I had unwittingly familiarized myself with all the famous hackers,
我不知不觉就熟悉了19世纪所有著名的

04:09.332 --> 04:12.381
dosers and severers of the 19th century.
黑客 病毒和凶徒

04:13.503 --> 04:17.303
Faces that would've frightened the Ripper.
他们令开膛手杰克都胆战心惊

04:21.845 --> 04:24.223
Many a long night I spent there,
我在这度过了许多个漫漫长夜

04:24.389 --> 04:27.518
drenched in thoughts of bloody murder.
满脑子都是血腥的谋杀

04:32.522 --> 04:37.653
I became particularly disturbed by a man I called The Hendon Ogre.
那个被我称作亨顿食人魔的男人尤其让我惴惴不安

04:37.861 --> 04:41.911
A maniac from North London who had boiled the arsenic out of fly papers
这个自伦敦北部的疯子 用灭蝇纸熬成了砒霜

04:42.115 --> 04:45.961
and introduced the result into his lodger's broth.
倒进了他房客的肉汤里

04:46.119 --> 04:48.622
I'd lie awake for hours, thinking of the brute,
我久久不能入睡 想着这个畜生

04:48.789 --> 04:51.542
terrified someone was slipping arsenic into my diet.
害怕有人也会把砒霜倒进我的饭里

04:53.418 --> 04:56.763
In the mornings, I'd inspect grapefruit and milk bottle tops
早上起来 我会仔细检查我的葡萄柚和牛奶瓶盖

04:56.963 --> 05:00.888
looking for evidence of interference with syringes.
寻找注射器插过的痕迹

05:01.051 --> 05:05.602
Trivial events became vital clues in the detection of my assassin.
琐碎的事情在我对暗杀的侦查之下都变成了重要的线索

05:10.268 --> 05:14.273
If the telephone rang at half past four, I'd look at the clock and say,
如果4点半的时候电话响了 我会看看钟 说到

05:14.481 --> 05:18.987
"it was half past four when the telephone rang that fateful evening.
"在那个关键的夜晚 电话在4点半的时候响起

05:19.152 --> 05:21.200
How could anyone have known at the time
怎么会有人知道此刻

05:21.363 --> 05:25.038
how important that telephone call was to become?"
这个电话会成为多么重要的线索?"

05:27.118 --> 05:30.463
My situation became unbearable.
我的情况实在是忍无可忍了

05:31.331 --> 05:34.084
I suspected everyone and everything.
我怀疑所有的人事物

05:35.460 --> 05:37.679
Innocent passersby.
包括无辜的路人

05:37.879 --> 05:40.758
Creeks in the corridor.
走廊上的克里克人(美国印第安部落)

05:41.633 --> 05:47.356
Bumps in the night got so bad, I started plugging my head shut.
在夜里 大脑思绪太过活跃 我不得不堵住它

05:47.889 --> 05:53.362
But I'd soon have to get up and check for killers in the bathroom,
不过 用不了多久 我就得起床来检查浴室里有没有杀手

05:53.520 --> 05:55.614
in the kitchen...
还要看看厨房里...

05:56.690 --> 05:58.613
in the fridge,
冰箱里

05:58.775 --> 06:00.368
or in the hallway,
还有走廊上

06:00.569 --> 06:02.742
where they kept a low profile,
他们会低调行事

06:02.946 --> 06:09.079
crawling about in the shadows, lurking behind creaky doors.
潜伏在吱吱作响的门后面 躲在暗处伺机而动 

06:13.081 --> 06:15.129
Ah!
啊!

06:15.292 --> 06:18.421
Bloody windows, bloody draughts.
该死的窗户 该死的空气

06:39.900 --> 06:41.902
Oh, God, come on.
噢 天哪 别这样了

06:43.695 --> 06:45.697
Argh!
啊!

06:50.410 --> 06:56.417
This fear that I would be murdered all began sometime before.
这种担心被谋杀的感觉始于不久之前

06:56.625 --> 06:58.969
At lunch, to be exact.
确切的说 是在某个午饭时间

06:59.127 --> 07:01.129
The day I saw my literary agent...
我去见我的文稿代理人的那天...

07:01.338 --> 07:03.306
- Newspaper?  - Clair De Grunwald.
- 报纸要吗?  - 她就是克莱尔·古伦王德

07:03.506 --> 07:05.099
- Thanks.  - No problem.
- 谢了  - 不客气

07:05.300 --> 07:11.398
She'd arranged to meet me at a respectable establishment in SoHo.
她安排我们在索豪区的一家高档餐厅见面

07:12.140 --> 07:14.518
You like newspaper?
要读报吗?

07:26.613 --> 07:30.243
- Shall I bring sir the wine list?  - Yes. Okay.
- 需要我为您把酒单拿来吗?  - 嗯 好的

07:30.450 --> 07:32.828
Pleasure.
不客气

07:45.674 --> 07:48.553
"The body was found in the East End of London,
"在东伦敦找到一具尸体

07:48.718 --> 07:51.722
but the Hanoi Handshake is the unmistakable calling card
但是河内握手信号表明这显然是

07:51.930 --> 07:54.024
of a Vietnamese gang killing.
一群越南人造成的杀戮

07:56.685 --> 07:58.813
According to one unnamed police source
一位不愿意透露姓名的警方人员表示

07:59.020 --> 08:01.773
downtown Hackney, also known as Little Vietnam
有着小越南之称的哈克尼区

08:01.982 --> 08:04.952
is now a bloody jungle...
现在完全是一个有组织犯罪的...

08:05.777 --> 08:08.826
of organized crime.
血腥丛林

08:08.989 --> 08:11.242
The missing fingers have yet to be found."
失踪的手指目前还没有找到"

08:11.741 --> 08:13.084
Newspaper?
要报纸吗?

08:23.628 --> 08:25.380
- Whoa, hey, no...  - Sir.
- 哇 嘿 别...  - 先生

08:25.588 --> 08:27.761
- No, it... Please...  - Jack?
- 别动... 拜托了...  - 杰克 你怎么了?

08:27.966 --> 08:29.889
- Clair.  - Under the table already?
- 嘿 克莱尔  - 看来你已经醉了?

08:30.093 --> 08:31.436
It's not even 12:00.
还不到12点呢

08:31.761 --> 08:33.354
- No, I...  - I'm sorry.
- 不 我只是...  - 抱歉

08:33.554 --> 08:35.398
I'm afraid I only have an hour.
恐怕我只能给你一个小时

08:35.597 --> 08:37.645
I've got to go meet Ragsie Lawrence.
我还要去见瑞格丝·劳伦斯

08:37.851 --> 08:41.071
Remember Ragsie? The dancing dyke?
还记得瑞格丝·劳伦斯吗? 就是那个跳舞的同性恋

08:41.270 --> 08:44.241
She's just been made commissioning editor at the BBC.
她刚刚成为英国广播电台的责任编辑

08:44.441 --> 08:47.035
Can you believe it?
你信吗?

08:47.318 --> 08:51.789
Never underestimate a hunchback, that's what I say.
所以说 永远不要低估任何人

08:51.948 --> 08:55.669
- Are you staying there all lunch?  - No, sorry.
- 你要那么坐着吃午饭吗?  - 不 抱歉

08:57.370 --> 08:59.213
Anyway...
不管这么说...

09:02.751 --> 09:06.881
It's good timing. I can tell her how busy you are with your murders.
时机不错 我可以告诉她你正忙着编纂你的谋杀案呢

09:07.047 --> 09:08.799
- Up to my elbows.  - Good.
- 忙得不可开交啊  - 很好

09:09.174 --> 09:11.927
- Do you have a title?  - "Decades of Death".
- 想好题目了吗?  - "死亡年代"

09:12.427 --> 09:14.429
- Chilling.  - Well, if you want murder...
- 够酷  - 其实 如果想写谋杀案...

09:14.596 --> 09:16.849
then Victorian Britain is the golden age.
英国维多利亚女王时代绝对是黄金时期

09:17.015 --> 09:20.394
I think murder's lost its sense of theatre. What do we have now?
我觉得谋杀已经失去了剧场的感觉 我们现在有什么?

09:20.560 --> 09:23.109
- It's just like kids...  - Mindless violence?
- 就像孩子那么幼稚...  - 愚蠢的暴力?

09:23.313 --> 09:27.034
Exactly. Yes. Killers don't put any thought into their murders anymore.
对 就是愚蠢的暴力 杀手都不再好好谋划他们的罪行了

09:27.233 --> 09:30.112
- Have you heard of Long Ear?  - Can't say I have, no.
- 你听说过长耳朵的故事吗?  - 这我可真不知道

09:31.071 --> 09:34.245
Terrifying Polish plumber who hacked off a Frenchman's head.
一个可怕地波兰水管工 他砍掉了一个法国人的脑袋

09:34.407 --> 09:38.082
Disposed of the limbs, but couldn't think of what to do with the head.
肢解了四肢 却不知道如何处理这个头颅

09:38.244 --> 09:40.747
Eventually he utilized his gas-fired crucible,
最后他利用燃气的坩埚

09:40.914 --> 09:44.134
filled the mouth with lead, slung the thing in the river.
把他嘴里塞满了铅 把头颅扔到了河里

09:44.292 --> 09:46.044
Can you imagine?
你能想象出来吗?

09:46.836 --> 09:50.682
I'm sorry, sir. This is a non-smoking restaurant. Thank you.
抱歉 先生 我们这里禁烟 谢谢合作

09:51.758 --> 09:55.353
- Are you ready to order, madam?  - Do you know what you're having?
- 女士 您准备点餐了吗?  - 想好要吃什么了吗?

09:55.678 --> 09:57.897
I'll just have a beer. I'm not very hungry.
喝酒就行了 我还不太饿

09:58.098 --> 10:01.102
- One beer.  - This is my treat, darling.
- 一瓶啤酒  - 这顿我来请 亲爱的

10:01.309 --> 10:05.405
Well, then I will have the chicory salad with asparagus croutons,
这样的话 那再给我来一份苦苣沙拉 开胃菜还要芦笋面包丁

10:05.605 --> 10:08.779
chorizo and poached egg to start.
西班牙辣香肠和荷包蛋

10:08.983 --> 10:11.281
Followed by the salmon and leek fish cake
然后上一份鲑鱼韭菜蛋糕

10:11.444 --> 10:15.074
with mushy peas, chips and chive cream. Thank you. Lovely.
再有豌豆糊 薯条和细香葱 多谢了 亲爱的

10:15.240 --> 10:16.787
People love a good murder.
人们总是喜欢精彩的谋杀案

10:16.991 --> 10:20.621
I began to tell Clair about my good friend Professor Friedkin,
我开始跟克莱尔讲我的朋友弗莱德金教授的事

10:20.829 --> 10:24.379
author of an influential paper on the criminalstare,
曾写过一篇影响深远 讨论犯罪视角的论文

10:24.582 --> 10:30.055
an ocular condition that instantly identified a madman.
他有立刻辨认出疯子的锐利眼光

10:30.213 --> 10:32.386
Monsieur?
先生?

10:34.134 --> 10:36.011
Jack?
嘿 杰克?

10:37.387 --> 10:39.560
Jack? Jack?
杰克? 杰克 你怎么了?

10:44.060 --> 10:45.607
Jack?
嘿 杰克?

10:46.688 --> 10:48.065
- Jack?  - Yes. Sorry.
- 喂 没事吧?  - 没事 抱歉

10:48.273 --> 10:49.820
- Are you all right?  - Yes.
- 你没事吧?  - 嗯

10:50.024 --> 10:52.868
Yes. I'm sorry.
我没事 对不起

10:53.027 --> 10:56.201
- What was I talking about?  - The book.
- 我刚刚讲到哪了?  - 书

10:56.739 --> 11:00.084
- The criminal stare.  - Oh, yes, yes. the criminal stare.
- 犯罪视角  - 嗯 对 就是犯罪视角

11:00.285 --> 11:05.416
Yeah. I found... I've trawled through hundreds of these photographs and...
我发现了... 我网罗了数百张照片...

11:08.126 --> 11:12.381
Um, when you kill someone, when you take a life,
如果你杀了人 犯了杀戒

11:12.547 --> 11:17.769
you acquire these awful eyes, you know, like a shark or a chicken.
你就会有可怕的眼神 想想 就像鲨鱼或者鸡那样的眼神

11:17.927 --> 11:21.477
- How frightful.  - But it's not just a horror show.
- 真可怕  - 那不仅仅是场恐怖表演

11:21.681 --> 11:24.685
I've realised that's not the reason I have to write this.
我意识到这不是我写下这些的原因

11:24.893 --> 11:28.523
No, it's a detective story, you see, about how they become killers.
这是个侦探故事 讲述他们如何成为杀手的

11:28.730 --> 11:32.451
How do they get there? What fills them with need to victimize and kill?
他们如何到那里去的? 是什么驱使他们进行杀戮和破坏?

11:32.650 --> 11:35.494
- Why choose mass murder?  - Why not become a writer?
- 为什么选择大规模屠杀?  - 为什么不当个作家呢?

11:35.653 --> 11:38.827
Well, actually, writers and serial killers are very similar.
其实 作家和连环杀手是很相似的

11:39.032 --> 11:40.534
They're practically brothers.
他们实际上就是兄弟

11:40.700 --> 11:43.499
Hemingway says, “What do you need to become a writer?
海明威说过"成为一名作家需要些什么?

11:43.661 --> 11:46.665
An unhappy childhood." It's the same thing with serial killers.
一个悲惨的童年" 成为连环杀手也是如此

11:46.831 --> 11:49.209
Whatever happened to the hedgehog?
刺猬怎么了?

11:49.375 --> 11:51.673
- What?  - He had to cross the road...
- 什么?  - 他要穿过马路...

11:51.878 --> 11:54.427
and go into the woods, but he was afraid.
进去丛林 但是他害怕

11:55.048 --> 11:58.177
- Harold the Hedgehog?  - Harold the Hedgehog.
- 刺猬哈罗德?  - 对 刺猬哈罗德

11:58.384 --> 12:02.059
Dear little chap. Whatever happened to that story?
可爱的小故事 那个故事后来怎么样了?

12:02.222 --> 12:04.975
- You never finished him.  - He nearly finished me.
- 你都没完结他  - 他差点了结了我

12:05.183 --> 12:07.106
He wrecked my marriage, prickly cunt.
这个多刺的小混蛋 他毁了我的婚姻

12:08.228 --> 12:10.697
No, he did, Clair. I'm sorry, the stress of it.
他就是这么干了 克莱尔 抱歉 这就是重点

12:10.897 --> 12:14.652
Drove Catherine out of my life. What do you wanna talk about him for?
他让凯瑟琳离开了我的生活 你还提他干嘛?

12:14.817 --> 12:18.367
Darling, I'm just thinking you need to earn some money, that's all.
亲爱的 我只是认为你需要赚点钱了 就这样

12:18.571 --> 12:20.790
This death thing could take a while.
写死亡这种事还需要一段时间来完成

12:20.949 --> 12:22.872
Timmy the Tortoise can't pay the bills.
小乌龟蒂姆又不赚钱

12:23.034 --> 12:26.413
I don't want him to. I didn't mean to become a children's author.
我也没想用他付账 我没想要成为儿童作家

12:26.579 --> 12:29.799
- It was a terrible accident.  - It was your destiny.
- 那只是个意外  - 那就是你的命运

12:29.958 --> 12:34.213
Look, why not rattle off a little bedtime story, mm?
听着 为什么不写点床边故事呢 怎么样?

12:34.379 --> 12:37.303
- Timmy goes to the seaside perhaps?  - Oh, God.
- 也许写蒂姆去海滩的故事?  - 天哪

12:37.507 --> 12:39.350
Or Harold. How did it start?
要么写哈罗德 这是怎么开始的?

12:40.969 --> 12:44.314
"Once upon a time, there was a hedgehog called Harold
"从前 有一只小刺猬叫做哈罗德

12:44.472 --> 12:47.942
who lived in a bush."
他住在灌木丛里"

12:49.852 --> 12:52.321
Or Little Johnny Rabbit.
要么就写小兔子约翰尼

12:52.480 --> 12:56.906
The world is dying for another Little Johnny Rabbit.
这个世界肯定会为另一只小兔子约翰尼而倾倒的

12:57.110 --> 12:58.987
Little Johnny Rabbit is dead.
小兔子约翰尼死了

12:59.195 --> 13:01.414
So is Timmy, so is the fucking hedgehog.
蒂姆也死了 刺猬也死了

13:01.572 --> 13:04.667
They're lying in the road, covered in blood. I killed them.
他们横尸马路 躺在血泊之中 我杀了他们

13:04.826 --> 13:07.045
Tell that to the kids.
就这么跟孩子们说

13:14.502 --> 13:17.130
Darling, we're going to make this work.
亲爱的 我们一起来解决

13:17.338 --> 13:20.558
Just try not to worry too much, and take care of yourself.
别太担心了 照顾好自己

13:20.717 --> 13:22.685
You know me better than anyone, Clair.
你比任何人都了解我 克莱尔

13:22.885 --> 13:27.140
Yes, I do. You're a workaholic and you're sensitive.
是的 我知道你是个工作狂 而且很敏感

13:27.307 --> 13:31.062
I don't wanna see you go over the edge like what's-his-name.
我不想看见你像书里的人那样走极端

13:34.689 --> 13:37.943
Clair's concerns about me proved justified.
克莱尔对我的担忧是正确的

13:38.109 --> 13:42.285
Three weeks on and Long Ear's head was playing on my mind.
三个星期过去了 长耳朵的脑袋一直盘旋在我脑海里

13:44.073 --> 13:45.700
Life was hellish,
生活很凶残

13:45.867 --> 13:48.620
but it was just about to get a hell of a lot worse.
日子却越来越糟糕

13:58.671 --> 14:01.140
Come on then, you bastards!
来呀 你这个混蛋!

14:02.133 --> 14:05.012
Aaaaaargh!
啊啊啊啊啊!

14:06.637 --> 14:08.639
My knife.
我的刀呢
01888

14:23.112 --> 14:25.114
Ah!
啊!

14:56.521 --> 14:59.195
You mad bastard.
你这个疯子

16:29.113 --> 16:31.115
Argh!
啊!

16:47.965 --> 16:50.013
Oh, God.
天哪

16:58.768 --> 17:00.816
Oh, I got an hour.
我还有1个小时

17:08.069 --> 17:10.070
The flying eye.
飞行监视器呀

17:11.321 --> 17:15.167
Oh, someone's on the loose.
哎呦 有人逍遥法外了

17:17.369 --> 17:21.500
It was 5:00 when the telephone rang that fateful evening.
那个关键的晚上 电话在五点时响起

17:21.665 --> 17:23.088
Shit, I could...
该死 我能...

17:31.467 --> 17:33.720
Hello?
你们好?

17:33.886 --> 17:35.229
Happy Christmas.
圣诞节快乐

17:35.388 --> 17:37.265
Happy Christmas.
圣诞节快乐

17:38.724 --> 17:41.694
- What do you want?  - We're singing carols.
- 你们想要什么?  - 我们在唱颂歌

17:41.852 --> 17:44.071
Yeah, I can see that.
恩 看得出来

17:44.230 --> 17:47.074
Well, ain't you gonna come out and hear us then, bruv?
大叔 你不出来听我们唱歌吗?

17:47.233 --> 17:50.783
No, I can hear you perfectly well from up here. Thank you.
不了 我在这就能听到 谢了

17:50.945 --> 17:54.119
We've been out for ages and no one's given us nuffink yet.
我们出来很久了 不过没人给我们吃的

17:54.282 --> 17:58.253
Well, honestly, I think you should perhaps work on your repertoire.
老实说 我觉得你们应该多努力表演你们的节目

17:59.787 --> 18:02.916
- Our what?  - Sorry I can't help you. Good night.
- 我们的什么?  - 抱歉帮不了你们 晚安

18:03.124 --> 18:04.967
But it's for Save the Children.
这可是为了拯救孩子们

18:05.167 --> 18:08.922
Kids who ain't got no food, Nintendo or nothing, bruv.
那些孩子没有食物 没有游戏 什么都没有呀 大叔

18:15.511 --> 18:17.263
All right, all right. Wait there.
好吧 好吧 等等

18:17.430 --> 18:19.774
- I'm coming down.  - Yes.
- 我马上下来  - 耶

18:27.898 --> 18:31.368
You gonna open up this door, then, or what, bruv?
你会打开门的吧 然后呢 大叔?

18:32.486 --> 18:35.114
Um, I tell you what I'm gonna do.
我告诉你们然后怎么办

18:35.281 --> 18:37.784
I'm gonna put some loose change into this sock
我把一些零钱放在这个袜子里

18:37.992 --> 18:41.838
and then I'm gonna feed it through the letter box.
我把袜子从信箱塞出去

18:43.331 --> 18:46.301
- Did you get that?  - Is it clean?
- 听明白没?  - 袜子干净吗?

18:46.500 --> 18:48.878
- Is it what?  - Is it clean?
- 什么?  - 干净吗?

18:49.086 --> 18:50.633
Is the sock clean, bruv?
袜子是干净的吗 大叔?

18:50.838 --> 18:54.308
Well, it's not box fresh, if that's what you mean.
其实 不是新拆封的 如果你们是这个意思的话

18:54.508 --> 18:56.476
Do you want this money or not?
你们想不想要钱啊?

18:58.929 --> 19:00.647
Oh, God.
天哪

19:01.015 --> 19:02.358
Who are you?
你是谁?

19:02.558 --> 19:04.401
- You there?  - Yes. Yes.
- 还在吗?  - 恩 还在

19:04.602 --> 19:08.197
I just... Stand back, okay? Stand back.
我只是... 往后退 好吧? 后退

19:10.274 --> 19:12.652
Christ, can't you see I'm not in?
天哪 难道你不知道我不在家吗?

19:15.488 --> 19:18.287
Okay. Get ready.
好了 准备好

19:18.491 --> 19:20.789
I'm opening my flap.
我要开信箱了噢

19:22.912 --> 19:25.256
Here it comes. Gently does it.
来了 轻点拿

19:25.456 --> 19:27.424
Gently.
轻点

19:27.583 --> 19:30.928
God in heaven, will you just fuck off and give me some peace?
我的神啊 你就不能滚开 让我清净清净?

19:31.087 --> 19:34.591
Hey, wait. Just come back!
嘿 等等 快回来!

19:34.757 --> 19:38.182
Oi! What about my sock? You little thieving, you...
啊! 我的袜子怎么办? 你们这些小偷 你们...

19:40.513 --> 19:43.357
You... you did this.
你们... 你们居然这样

19:43.683 --> 19:45.902
You wanna hear my voice, you sick fuck?
你想听听我的声音吗 你这个变态?

19:46.060 --> 19:48.108
Hear this.
听着吧

19:48.270 --> 19:51.274
- Hello?  - Jack, it's Clair.
- 喂?  - 杰克 我是克莱尔

19:51.440 --> 19:52.987
Hello?
喂?

19:53.192 --> 19:55.115
- Jack, it's Clair.  - Clair.
- 杰克 我是克莱尔  - 克莱尔啊

19:55.319 --> 19:58.573
Why haven't you been answering? I've been calling for hours.
你为什么总不接电话? 我都打了几个小时了

19:58.739 --> 20:01.618
- I thought you were a wrong number.  - Well, listen.
- 我以为是打错的  - 好吧 听着

20:01.826 --> 20:06.332
I've just had a very excited man on the phone.
我刚刚和一个很激动的男人讲完电话

20:06.497 --> 20:09.341
- Have you?  - Yes. He's read your treatment...
- 是吗?  - 恩 他读了你的作品...

20:09.500 --> 20:13.505
for "Decades of Death" and he's very excited by your ideas.
那份"死亡年代" 他对你的构思很感兴趣

20:13.713 --> 20:16.307
He wants to meet you tonight at eight o'clock.
他今晚八点想见见你

20:16.465 --> 20:18.092
Oh.
哦

20:18.259 --> 20:21.308
- I see. Eight o'clock?  - He's off to New York tomorrow.
- 我知道了 8点?  - 他明天要去纽约

20:21.470 --> 20:25.100
- It's imperative you see him.  - Why is it imperative?
- 你势必得见他一面  - 为什么必须见?

20:25.266 --> 20:27.519
Because he's Harvey Humphries.
因为他是哈维·汉弗莱斯

20:27.685 --> 20:30.780
- Harvey Humphries? Who's he?  - Head of scripts.
- 哈维·汉弗莱斯? 他是谁?  - 出版界的领头人物

20:31.689 --> 20:35.034
Clair, look, can I see him when he comes back from New York?
克莱尔 我能不能等他从纽约回来再见面?

20:35.234 --> 20:37.828
Because I've not been sleeping very well and...
因为最近我睡得不太好...

20:37.987 --> 20:42.117
Jack, he's genuinely excited. The arrangements have all been made.
杰克 他非常有诚意 时间都安排好了

20:42.283 --> 20:45.287
Tonight, eight o'clock, 100 Humbolt Mews.
今晚8点 洪堡街100号

20:47.121 --> 20:50.921
100 Humbolt Mews, eight...
洪堡街100号 8点...

20:51.083 --> 20:54.257
- That's in one hour and 47 minutes.  - Wear a suit, please.
- 那不就还剩1小时47分钟吗  - 请穿西装来

20:54.420 --> 20:56.673
- I don't have any suits.  - Wear a clean shirt.
- 我没西装  - 那就穿件干净的T恤

20:56.839 --> 20:59.467
They're all dirty. I'm down to my last sock.
衣服都脏了 最后一只袜子都没了

20:59.675 --> 21:02.428
Then you'll have to go to the launderette, won't you?
那你就去自助洗衣店 行吧?

21:02.636 --> 21:05.389
What? A launderette? Are you serious?
什么? 自助洗衣店? 你说真的?

21:05.556 --> 21:07.229
Of course I am. What's the problem?
是呀 有什么问题?

21:07.391 --> 21:11.988
It's just... You're asking a lot, Clair, okay?
只是... 你要求太多了 克莱尔 知道吗?

21:12.146 --> 21:15.275
I don't do launderettes. Never have done, never will.
我从来不去自助洗衣 以前不会 将来也不会

21:15.441 --> 21:17.114
It's no place for a man like me.
那地方不适合我这样的男人

21:17.318 --> 21:20.538
Exposing your most intimate articles in front of strangers.
怎么能把最私密的物品展露在陌生人面前

21:20.696 --> 21:24.917
- Stop it, you're being ridiculous.  - You know me, Clair. I'm sensitive.
- 闭嘴 你太搞笑了  - 你了解我的 克莱尔 我很敏感

21:25.075 --> 21:28.420
- I've never even bought toilet roll.  - All right, enough.
- 我甚至都不买成卷的厕纸  - 行了 够了吧

21:29.413 --> 21:33.043
Jack, I've worked very hard getting your script to the right people
杰克 我一直很尽力地把你的手稿给合适的人看

21:33.209 --> 21:36.088
and I'm afraid there's no interest.
恐怕没人有兴趣

21:36.253 --> 21:40.383
I said nothing because I didn't want to disturb you. That's the reality.
我什么都没说是因为不想打扰你写作 但这就是事实

21:40.549 --> 21:42.222
I can't see any other options.
我只能说 你别无选择

21:42.384 --> 21:44.978
It's Humphries or bust.
要么去见汉弗莱斯 要么破产

21:47.056 --> 21:49.980
- I understand.  - Good.
- 明白了  - 很好

21:50.142 --> 21:52.440
Call and let me know how it goes, darling.
打电话告诉我事情进展 亲爱的

22:03.155 --> 22:09.538
And so it was that I first came to hear the name Harvey Humphries.
这是我第一次听到哈维·汉弗莱斯的名字

22:09.745 --> 22:12.749
I had sat in every head of scripts department in London,
我曾经拜访过伦敦每一家出版社的头儿

22:12.915 --> 22:16.089
listening to these twats full of white wine and arugula,
听这些吃饱喝足了的笨蛋们讲话

22:16.252 --> 22:18.300
but I had never heard of this man.
但我从来没听过这个人的名字

22:18.504 --> 22:21.758
"Harvey Humphries of Humbolt Mews."
"洪堡街的哈维·汉弗莱斯"

22:21.966 --> 22:24.219
I didn't like the sound of it.
我不喜欢这个发音

22:24.385 --> 22:28.435
The name seemed innocent enough, but there was something that jarred.
这个名字看起来很天真 内里却很刺耳

22:28.639 --> 22:32.394
It might be the "Harvey Humphries Humbolt" bit that was worrying me.
可能是"洪堡街的哈维·汉弗莱斯"让我感觉不爽吧

22:32.601 --> 22:35.354
But I had a friend, Garry Gordon in Garrick Street.
不过我有个朋友 住在格里克大街的盖里戈登

22:35.563 --> 22:37.565
And he'd never caused me any problem.
他就从来没让我感到不舒服过

22:37.773 --> 22:39.366
No.
不

22:39.775 --> 22:42.949
It was something stronger than just a repetition of the H.
并不是简单的连续H字头

22:43.112 --> 22:46.207
It was more a sensation of having heard Harvey Humphries
感觉更像是从一个臭名昭彰的角度 

22:46.407 --> 22:50.037
in some unsavory context.
听过哈维·汉弗莱斯的名字

22:51.871 --> 22:53.214
Harvey.
哈维

22:54.748 --> 22:57.092
It was the Harvey.
是那个哈维

23:06.510 --> 23:10.640
Harvey was the middle name of Dr. Hawley Harvey Crippen,
哈维是霍利·哈维·克里平医生的中间名

23:10.848 --> 23:13.567
the Yank Who'd spent all night in the basement
那个住在N5区 新月希尔德劳普大街39号

23:13.767 --> 23:18.568
of 39 Hilldrop Crescent, N5 separating his wife.
花了一整夜在地下室分尸自己妻子的那个人

23:19.064 --> 23:21.442
He'd done her in lime.
他用石灰泡着她

23:22.109 --> 23:23.736
Crippen had come from America.
克里平是从美国来的

23:23.944 --> 23:26.447
Humphries was going to America within hours
汉弗莱斯在见过我之后

23:26.614 --> 23:28.582
of completing his business with me.
没几个小时也要到美国去

23:29.909 --> 23:32.253
Was Humphries related to Crippen?
汉弗莱斯和克里平有关系吗?

23:32.453 --> 23:36.503
Far-fetched as it might seem to others, it was not impossible.
有点牵强 并不是不可能

23:36.707 --> 23:39.176
Crippen was an American. Yes.
克里平是美国人 对

23:39.376 --> 23:40.753
And so was Humphries.
而且汉弗莱斯也是

23:40.961 --> 23:44.591
Surely it was more than a coincidence that a man going to America
一个马上去美国的人会被这个是叫做"死亡年代"的题目所吸引

23:44.798 --> 23:47.722
should be excited by a title like "Decades of Death"
这一切肯定不仅仅是个巧合

23:47.927 --> 23:52.728
and have the middle name of one of the most famous killers of the lot.
而且还和最著名凶手的中间名一样

23:55.100 --> 23:56.977
No.
不

23:57.895 --> 23:59.363
No, no, no.
不 不 不

23:59.563 --> 24:04.410
Facts like that are beyond the realm of coincidence.
这样的事实绝不仅仅是巧合

24:28.509 --> 24:31.103
Hello? Who's there?
喂? 你是哪位?

24:31.261 --> 24:33.263
Speak up, I can't hear you.
大点声 我听不见

24:35.599 --> 24:38.273
Oh, no. Clair's not here just now.
哦 没有 克莱尔现在不在

24:38.477 --> 24:41.151
This is Irene.
我是艾琳

24:41.313 --> 24:42.690
You want what?
你要什么?

24:42.898 --> 24:46.198
Harvey Humphries. Do you know of a man called Harvey Humphries?
哈维·汉弗莱斯 你认识叫哈维·汉弗莱斯的人吗?

24:46.402 --> 24:48.575
Think carefully before you answer, please.
仔细想好再回答 谢谢

24:48.779 --> 24:53.751
- A man's life may be at stake.  - Oh, I'll have to think about this.
- 性命攸关  - 哦 那我也考虑考虑

24:53.909 --> 24:56.708
Er, hold on a minute, love. Now...
呃 等等 亲爱的 现在...

24:56.870 --> 24:59.669
Can you tell her to call Jack back regarding Harvey Humphries?
你能让她就哈维·汉弗莱斯的事情给杰克打回来吗?

24:59.832 --> 25:01.960
Tell her it's a matter of life and death.
告诉她是性命攸关的大事

25:02.126 --> 25:04.470
- Life and death?  - Yes. Tell her that exactly.
- 性命攸关?  - 对 一字不差的告诉她

25:04.628 --> 25:07.131
- Thank you.  - Right. Will do, dear.
- 谢谢  - 好的 一定转达 亲爱的

25:07.339 --> 25:09.341
Okay, okay. Be rational, be rational.
好的 好的 冷静 冷静

25:09.550 --> 25:13.225
Clair was obviously not in her office, so she must've telephoned you from home.
克莱尔不在办公室 所以她肯定是从家给你打电话的

25:13.429 --> 25:15.648
But as you don't have her private number,
可是因为你没有她的私人号码

25:15.848 --> 25:19.273
and she's ex-directory, there's no way you can call her back.
而且她也不在号码记录上 你没办法给她打回去

25:19.435 --> 25:22.564
I have to trust it was Clair, and that she meant no malice.
我只能相信刚才打电话的就是克莱尔 而且她没有恶意

25:22.771 --> 25:25.399
After all, she has no reason to wish me any harm.
毕竟 她没理由想让我受伤害

25:25.566 --> 25:29.821
She had no way of knowing a man related to a murderer.
她不可能认识一个与凶案有关的人

25:29.987 --> 25:33.332
Only a highly suspicious, paranoid cynic...
只有生性多疑 偏执妄想的愤青...

25:33.532 --> 25:36.832
Or someone like me, with an eye for clues and patterns
或是像我一样 有双能发觉蛛丝马迹的慧眼

25:37.036 --> 25:38.879
could possibly connect the dots.
能把每个疑点都联系起来

25:39.079 --> 25:42.959
Could see the truth staring him in the face.
看到他真人便知道真相

25:43.167 --> 25:47.217
That Harvey Humphries is in fact Hawley Harvey Crippen's grandson.
事实上哈维·汉弗莱斯就是霍利·哈维·克里平的孙子

25:47.379 --> 25:49.131
No more questions, Your Honor.
没问题了 法官大人

25:49.298 --> 25:51.517
Ah!
啊!

25:55.971 --> 25:57.644
Right. That does it.
好了 我可受够了

25:57.848 --> 26:00.271
Where's the superglue?
万能胶在哪?

26:00.476 --> 26:03.730
Right. You've done nothing but terrorise me for weeks.
这呢 你们除了恐吓我好几个礼拜还能做什么

26:03.937 --> 26:05.905
And I've had enough. I've had enough.
我受够了 彻底受够了

26:06.065 --> 26:08.568
Take that, and that, and that, and that.
吃胶水吧 吃啊 吃啊 吃啊

26:08.776 --> 26:12.622
Take that, take this, take this.
给我粘住 粘住 粘住

26:14.698 --> 26:17.372
Take that. You didn't expect that, did you?
粘牢你 你没想到吧?

26:17.576 --> 26:20.750
Well, expect the unexpected, mate.
学会接受现实吧 伙计

26:28.378 --> 26:30.380
God, that's quick.
天哪 这么快就粘牢了

26:44.436 --> 26:47.940
Hello? Anyone home?
您好? 有人在家吗?

26:50.067 --> 26:52.069
Yes? Hello?
在啊 怎么了?

26:52.236 --> 26:54.989
Are you the gentleman in Flat 3?
您是住在3单元的先生吗?

26:55.197 --> 26:56.540
Who is this?
你是谁?

26:56.740 --> 27:00.290
Community Support Police Officer Perkins, sir.
我是社区支援警官珀金斯 先生

27:01.120 --> 27:03.248
Good evening. How can I help you?
晚上好 找我有什么事吗?

27:03.413 --> 27:06.713
Oh, no cause for alarm. Just a routine call, sir.
哦 别紧张 只是个例行询问 先生

27:06.875 --> 27:12.632
Some of the kids over on the estate said you might be in some distress.
社区里的几个孩子说你好像很痛苦

27:16.510 --> 27:18.262
How interesting.
真有意思

27:18.428 --> 27:21.853
And what might I be distressed about?
他们说我为什么痛苦呢?

27:22.057 --> 27:23.980
Well, I have no idea, sir.
我不知道 先生

27:24.184 --> 27:26.562
Are you in any distress?
您痛苦吗?

27:26.728 --> 27:30.107
No, I'm fine. I'm about to do some washing and then go to bed.
没有 我很好 我正要洗衣服然后去睡觉

27:30.274 --> 27:32.493
Oh, well. Just so you know,
哦 好吧 那跟您说声

27:32.693 --> 27:36.573
we're out on the beat if you ever need assistance.
如果您需要帮助 我们就在外面巡逻

27:36.738 --> 27:38.991
I'm just across the road.
我就在马路对面

27:41.994 --> 27:43.337
Jesus Christ.
天啊

27:43.537 --> 27:47.041
Sorry, sir, sorry. Sorry. I was just checking you were...
对不起 先生 对不起 我只想确认下您没事...

27:47.207 --> 27:49.585
Yeah, well, I'm very sorry to bother you, sir.
很抱歉打扰您 先生

27:49.793 --> 27:52.512
Er, I'll let you get back to your laundry.
您快去洗衣吧

27:53.755 --> 27:56.178
Policeman, my ass.
警察 去他大爷的

27:57.092 --> 27:59.094
He was looking for something.
他刚才在找东西

27:59.887 --> 28:01.855
What was he up to?
他到底来干吗?

28:02.556 --> 28:03.933
Jesus, nowhere's safe.
天哪 没地方是安全的

28:04.641 --> 28:08.612
Okay, Humphries, you want my script? You can have it.
好吧 汉弗莱斯 你想要我的剧本? 我都给你

28:08.812 --> 28:11.190
If it means I finally get paid decent money
如果最后我能拿到合理的报酬

28:11.356 --> 28:13.734
and get out of Hackney, you're on.
搬出哈克尼区 你会拿到剧本的

28:13.901 --> 28:16.120
Right. Where's my wardrobe?
好了 我的行头呢?

28:16.278 --> 28:19.248
I'll show you, Clair, I'll show you, Catherine,
我要让你看看 克莱尔 我要让你看看 凯瑟琳

28:19.406 --> 28:21.784
exactly what I am capable of. Oh!
让你们知道我有多厉害 哦!

28:21.950 --> 28:24.453
Jesus Christ.
我的天哪

28:26.288 --> 28:30.714
God. These aren't clothes, this is refuse.
上帝啊 这哪里是衣服 都成了垃圾

28:30.876 --> 28:34.005
I might as well take it and dig it in around the roses.
我最好拿上它们 埋在玫瑰旁边

28:34.796 --> 28:38.096
I'd do anything for a break right now, but not the launderette.
我现在就想休息会 才不想去洗衣房

28:38.258 --> 28:41.262
Not for Humphries, not for any other man.
不想为了汉弗莱斯 更不想为其他人去洗衣房

28:41.470 --> 28:45.441
Why should I? I've got everything I need here.
为什么非要去洗衣房? 我已经有我需要的全部东西

28:45.641 --> 28:49.441
I've got water, I've got soap, I've got drying facilities.
我有水 有肥皂 我还有烘干机

28:49.645 --> 28:51.067
I can do this, Jack.
我可以洗好的 杰克

28:51.271 --> 28:54.571
No more sleepless nights, no more scuttling around in the dark.
不再有失眠的夜晚 不再在黑暗中沉沦

28:54.733 --> 28:57.953
We'll meet this monster head-on. Well-armed and well-dressed.
我要装备齐全 穿戴整齐的迎头直面那个恶魔

28:59.071 --> 29:03.042
A quick thrash in the tub for you, my lovelies, then into the drier.
迅速在浴盆打个滚后 我的小可爱们 再到烘干机里待会

29:04.409 --> 29:07.834
Right. A good 15 minutes on regular nine for the socks,
总共要十五分钟 袜子烘九分钟

29:08.038 --> 29:11.588
five minutes less for the pants, and we'll play the shirt by ear.
内裤四分钟 衬衣就看情况再定吧

29:11.750 --> 29:13.297
Now, that's cooking with gas.
十分有效率

29:22.302 --> 29:26.227
Here's how to play it. When you get to the meeting, refuse to sit down.
计划是这样 跟他会面的时候 不要坐下

29:26.431 --> 29:29.560
Refuse all drinks and cigarettes. Certainly all food.
婉拒所有的饮料和香烟 食物也一样

29:29.768 --> 29:31.520
The meeting will be conducted standing up.
站着会面就好

29:31.728 --> 29:34.902
And if he leaves the room to make a call, you go with him.
如果他出去打电话 就要跟着他

29:42.447 --> 29:44.324
I'll have a pretext for everything.
我有一个万能的借口

29:44.533 --> 29:49.164
I could take an apple or an onion into the meeting.
我要带个苹果或洋葱去见面

29:49.371 --> 29:50.714
Yeah, that'd work.
这样就好办了

29:50.914 --> 29:54.964
I could use it as a circumstance to show him my carving knife.
我可以据此创造出向他亮出雕刻刀的场景

29:58.297 --> 30:00.516
Ah! Ah!
啊! 黏住了!

30:00.674 --> 30:02.893
Ah! Ah! Ah! Ah!
哎呀! 啊!

30:03.051 --> 30:05.053
Argh!
惨了!

30:27.826 --> 30:30.875
Come on. Come on, come on.
拜托 快点啊 快下来吧

30:36.043 --> 30:37.761
Aow!
啊!

30:37.919 --> 30:40.217
Fuck. What the fuck am I supposed to do now?
妈的 我现在该怎么办?

30:40.422 --> 30:43.016
Cut my fucking hand off?
把手割下来吗?

30:46.803 --> 30:48.476
That's correct, officer.
对了 找警官

30:48.638 --> 30:52.142
When I saw the knife, I simply defended myself with the ice pick.
当我看到刀子的时候 我只是用碎冰锥来自卫

30:52.309 --> 30:55.563
I have no idea how the pick got stuck in the back of his neck.
我不知道锥子是怎么插进他的后颈的

30:55.729 --> 31:00.030
I put him in the bath tub because the blood was staining my Persian carpet.
我把他放进了浴缸里 因为血弄脏了我的波斯地毯

31:00.192 --> 31:02.194
Oh!
哦!

31:09.659 --> 31:11.252
Argh!
啊!

31:14.956 --> 31:16.458
Oh! Oh!
啊! 

31:31.765 --> 31:35.110
I'm not dead yet, you bastards.
我还没死呢 你个混蛋

31:38.605 --> 31:41.279
Come on, Jack, we can still do this.
走吧 杰克 我们依旧可以做到

31:41.441 --> 31:43.239
Against the odds, we can beat them.
迎难而上 我们能打倒他们

31:43.402 --> 31:46.702
Now, as I remember, this thing has some seriously deep pockets.
我记得 这衣服有很深的口袋

31:46.863 --> 31:49.867
Oh, yeah, yeah. Yeah, I can hide a knife in there.
哦 是的 我可以把刀子藏在这

31:50.075 --> 31:51.918
That's like Loch Ness in there.
这好像有尼斯湖水怪在里面

31:52.119 --> 31:55.123
You could hide a whole submarine in there if you wanna.
你甚至可以把整只水怪藏在这里

31:55.288 --> 31:58.007
I'll just keep my coat on. My hand on my ha'penny.
我要一直穿着外套 把手放在兜里铜板上

31:58.208 --> 32:01.132
Okay, don't let this guy psyche you out, all right?
好了 别让此人搞得你六神无主 知道吗?

32:01.336 --> 32:03.384
You're a writer, Jack, remember?
你是个作家 杰克 记住了吗?

32:03.547 --> 32:08.474
You can just outwit this two-bit Hollywood gangster.
你可以智取那个微不足道的好莱坞流氓

32:08.635 --> 32:10.057
Gangster?
流氓?

32:11.138 --> 32:14.768
Say she didn't throw it away. Please, please, please.
但愿她没把它扔掉 拜托 拜托 拜托

32:14.933 --> 32:17.652
Be in here. Be in here, be in here.
可得在这里啊 在这里 在这里

32:17.811 --> 32:20.155
Where are you? Where are you?
你在哪呢?

32:22.274 --> 32:26.745
"Uzilicious". My definitive gangsta rap compilation.
"由兹里血丝" 我的限量版帮匪说唱磁带

32:26.945 --> 32:29.289
Yeah, yeah.
太棒咯

32:29.614 --> 32:33.084
I remember I wooed Catherine with this shit.
我记得我就用它追求的凯瑟琳

32:33.243 --> 32:35.211
Hope it still works.
希望它没坏

32:40.041 --> 32:43.261
Good times, old friend. Good times.
真好啊 老朋友 想起从前好时光

32:43.420 --> 32:47.641
If you can get me through college, you can get me through anything.
你助我大学顺利毕业 你更会保佑我诸事顺利

32:58.185 --> 33:00.688
# I drop a old-school beat. # 
# 让我来段校园摇滚吧 # 

33:06.109 --> 33:08.487
# Yeah, yeah. # 
# 耶 耶 # 

33:08.778 --> 33:10.997
# Yeah, you wanna read my script, bitch? # 
# 你想看我剧本吗 婊子? # 

33:11.198 --> 33:14.042
# You wanna polish my script? You wanna polish my script? # 
# 你想完善我的剧本? 你想翻拍我的剧本? # 

33:14.201 --> 33:15.669
# Is that what you're saying? # 
# 是你说的吧? # 

33:15.827 --> 33:18.546
# What's up, bitch? You wanna polish my script? # 
# 怎么了 贱人? 你想改编我的剧本? # 

33:18.747 --> 33:21.717
# Oh, sure. Polish this, motherfucker. # 
# 好啊 那就看招吧 混蛋 # 

33:28.840 --> 33:31.059
# I'm gonna step up to a man called Humphries # 
# 我要走到汉弗莱斯这男人面前 # 

33:31.218 --> 33:33.266
# Wipe that shit up just like cream cheese # 
# 像擦掉奶油芝士一样轻易干掉那个贱人 # 

33:33.428 --> 33:35.681
# Up all night, y'all, workin' the mic, y'all # 
# 整夜都不睡 伙计们 唱起来 伙计们 #

33:35.889 --> 33:38.392
# Smoking my pipe, y'all, motherfucker # 
# 让我抽根烟 伙计们 他是个混蛋 # 

33:38.558 --> 33:40.560
# Catherine, this Jam goes out to you. # 
# 凯瑟琳 这首摇滚唱给你 # 

33:40.727 --> 33:42.400
# It's real, true dat from the heart. # 
# 这是我心底真情留白的录音 # 

33:42.604 --> 33:44.606
# I just wanna say you're my girl. # 
# 我想说你是我的女孩 # 

33:44.814 --> 33:46.441
- Shut up.  - # And I love you. # 
- 别唱了  - # 还有我爱你 # 

33:46.608 --> 33:48.030
Fuck.
妈的

33:50.695 --> 33:55.121
Who are you trying to fool, Jack? You're not a G-man, you're a tit.
你想骗谁呀 杰克? 你又不是联邦调查局的 你就是个窝囊废

33:59.204 --> 34:01.957
What's that smell?
什么味道?

34:02.123 --> 34:05.844
Smells like burning garbage.
闻起来像烧着的垃圾

34:10.882 --> 34:13.476
No! Not the socks! Not the socks!
不! 可别是袜子! 别是我的袜子!

34:15.594 --> 34:17.813
Argh! Damn it!
啊! 该死的!

34:19.641 --> 34:21.860
Oh!
哦!

34:22.018 --> 34:25.067
Oh! Oh, my eyes!
哦! 哦 我的眼睛!

34:31.777 --> 34:34.156
Oh, God, the pants have gone up.
哦 天啊 裤子都烧没了

34:35.864 --> 34:39.335
And you'll have to go to the launderette, won't you?
你该去洗衣房了吧?

34:40.579 --> 34:43.128
- A launderette, are you serious?  - Of course I am.
- 洗衣房 你没开玩笑?  - 我是认真的

34:43.331 --> 34:45.958
You'll have to go to the launderette, won't you?
你只能去洗衣房了 不是吗?

34:46.126 --> 34:48.504
You'll have to go to the launderette.
你必须去洗衣房

34:48.670 --> 34:50.138
Argh!
啊!

34:58.471 --> 35:01.224
Okay, let's cut the cake.
好了 切蛋糕吧

35:01.391 --> 35:04.395
Dad, can you answer that? It's Mr. Goofy. He's lost.
爸爸 你能接电话吗? 是古菲先生 他迷失了

35:04.561 --> 35:07.610
Mr. Goofy is on my office line?
古菲先生往我办公室打电话?

35:08.440 --> 35:09.908
Right, here we go.
好 我们开切

35:13.361 --> 35:15.113
Hello. This is Dr. Friedkin.
你好 我是弗莱德金医生

35:15.322 --> 35:17.370
You've got to help me, Dr. Friedkin.
你得帮帮我 弗莱德金医生

35:17.532 --> 35:19.034
Jack? Is this Jack?
杰克啊? 你是杰克吗?

35:19.242 --> 35:23.748
I can't take it anymore. I'm gonna buckle, I swear to God.
我再也受不了啦 我发誓 我就要死了

35:23.913 --> 35:27.008
Well, it's my grandson's birthday.
可今天是我孙子的生日

35:29.419 --> 35:31.638
A phobia of launderettes?
洗衣房恐惧症?

35:31.838 --> 35:33.715
Oh, Jack. That's a new one to me.
哦 杰克 我真没听说过

35:33.923 --> 35:36.392
Wait, I'm confused. Which case study is this?
等下 我糊涂了 这病源自哪个案例研究?

35:36.593 --> 35:39.938
It's not a case, Dr. Friedkin. It's me.
这不是案例 弗莱德金医生 是我的症状

35:40.138 --> 35:42.015
I'm the problem. It's me.
我有问题 是我

35:42.223 --> 35:46.729
Okay, okay, calm down. Just calm yourself.
好 冷静点 让自己保持镇定

35:46.936 --> 35:52.067
Jack, I want you to take a deep breath.
杰克 我要你先做个深呼吸

35:52.275 --> 35:54.027
Now, inhale...
现在 吸气...

35:55.737 --> 35:58.786
and exhale. That's right.
再呼气 很好

36:00.200 --> 36:03.170
Fill your entire body.
让氧气充满全身

36:03.370 --> 36:08.672
Imagine every cell being rinsed clean with life-giving oxygen.
想象着每个细胞都被让我们生存的氧气冲洗

36:09.250 --> 36:13.096
Do you have any clues where the origin of this phobia lies?
你知不知道这回的恐惧症是怎么引发的?

36:13.254 --> 36:15.507
I've had it all my life.
我一生都有这病

36:16.675 --> 36:19.144
I've tried to get on top of it.
我试着去驾驭恐惧

36:19.969 --> 36:22.347
I went to a washhouse when I was at college,
我大学的时候去过洗衣房

36:22.514 --> 36:24.437
but I was just so terrified,
可我实在太怕了

36:24.599 --> 36:26.897
I accidentally trapped my load in an OOO.
我不小心把衣服放进一台OOO里

36:28.144 --> 36:29.646
An OOO?
一台OOO?

36:29.854 --> 36:33.199
Yes. An out of order machine.
对 一台坏了的机器

36:33.400 --> 36:38.497
I was in there with about six months' of unimaginably sensitive material.
之后的六个月 暗无天日 我一直感觉自己还呆在那里

36:38.655 --> 36:41.124
The room gathered round, engineers were called.
房间里到处都是机器

36:41.324 --> 36:44.077
- It was a nightmare.  - No. I sympathize with you.
- 那是场噩梦啊  - 我同情你

36:44.285 --> 36:46.788
As unpleasant as the experience may have been,
就因为你的痛苦经历

36:46.996 --> 36:50.796
it cannot have been traumatic enough to create such a phobia.
才造成了创伤 引发出恐惧症

36:51.793 --> 36:54.012
It's ruining my life.
恐惧症毁了我整个人生

36:54.170 --> 36:57.140
Look, I can help you, but you must be completely honest.
听着 我能帮助你 可你要对我绝对诚实

36:57.340 --> 36:58.683
And you must trust me.
同时你必须信任我

36:59.676 --> 37:01.678
Close your eyes.
闭上眼睛

37:03.054 --> 37:05.728
I want you to take another deep breath
我要你再做一次深呼吸

37:05.932 --> 37:09.357
and imagine you are sitting here with me now in my office
想象自己正坐在我的办公室里

37:09.561 --> 37:12.064
having a consultation.
我在给你治疗

37:13.940 --> 37:16.489
Think of my office like a space capsule.
把我办公室想象成一个太空舱

37:16.693 --> 37:19.572
From here, we can go anywhere in the universe,
从这里 我们可以借由我们想象的力量

37:19.779 --> 37:24.706
in space and time, by the power of our mind.
飞去宇宙中的任何地方 无论时间和空间

37:24.909 --> 37:28.959
To your childhood, to your dreams.
想想你的童年 你的梦想

37:31.791 --> 37:35.421
Can you see the little hedgehog?
你能看见那只小刺猬吗?

37:35.837 --> 37:40.058
Frightened little hedgehog lives in an old hedgerow
受惊的小刺猬就住在教堂旁边的灌木丛里

37:40.258 --> 37:42.681
by the church. Can you see the spider?
你能看见那只蜘蛛吗?

37:42.886 --> 37:46.481
Clever spider. Waiting in the shadows.
聪明的蜘蛛 总在阴暗处中等待着

37:46.681 --> 37:49.525
And Mrs. Ladybird? And Mr. Rabbit?
还有瓢虫夫人? 兔子先生?

37:49.726 --> 37:53.276
How about old farmer...?
看到老农民了吗...?

38:05.366 --> 38:08.165
Did you have a happy childhood?
你的童年快乐吗?

38:10.955 --> 38:14.050
- What is your earliest memory?  - The orphanage on fire.
- 你最早的记忆是什么?  - 孤儿院起火

38:15.543 --> 38:18.171
- You're being facetious.  - No, I'm not, really.
- 你真会说笑  - 我没开玩笑 是真的

38:18.338 --> 38:21.808
The orphanage I was in caught fire. November the 5th, 1979.
我所在的孤儿院着火了 那是1979年11月5日

38:22.008 --> 38:24.557
Somebody let off a Roman candle in the dormitory.
有人在宿舍燃放了一支罗马烟火筒

38:24.761 --> 38:26.513
Luckily no one was hurt.
幸好无人伤亡

38:26.679 --> 38:29.478
You're an orphan? I'm sorry, I didn't...
你是个孤儿? 抱歉 我不知道...

38:29.682 --> 38:32.856
My mother abandoned me when I was 5 years old.
母亲在我五岁时抛弃了我

38:33.478 --> 38:36.527
She just packed a little suitcase for me one day
有一天她给我打包好一个小行李箱

38:36.815 --> 38:38.488
and disappeared.
之后她就消失了

38:41.110 --> 38:43.488
How did it happen, Jack?
为什么会那样 杰克?

38:44.906 --> 38:48.627
- It's all right to feel vulnerable.  - These pyjamas aren't helping.
- 感觉到无助是正常的  - 这些睡衣根本不起作用

38:49.994 --> 38:51.462
Try, Jack.
试试 杰克

38:52.121 --> 38:54.965
Try to go back.
试着回想从前

38:55.458 --> 38:59.508
The only memory I have of my mother is of a book she gave me.
我对母亲的唯一记忆就是她给我的一本书

38:59.712 --> 39:04.468
Fairy tales I suppose you call them. With these awful talking rodents.
你们管它叫童话故事 里面讲的都是讨厌的会说话的啮齿动物

39:04.676 --> 39:07.099
Look, truth is it doesn't bother me.
你看 事实不会让我不安

39:07.303 --> 39:10.056
I don't miss my mother because I don't remember her.
我不想念我母亲因为我不记得她

39:10.265 --> 39:14.236
I just... I'm sick of these irrational fears.
我只是... 受不了那些荒谬的恐惧

39:14.394 --> 39:17.898
Like the bloody launderette. It's stopping me from living my life.
就好像血腥的洗衣店 它阻碍了我的正常生活

39:18.064 --> 39:22.444
Well, you can do something about it. You're not a child anymore.
你可以克服的 你已经不是小孩了

39:22.652 --> 39:25.656
I once treated a girl who had a phobia of bananas.
我曾经治疗过一个有香蕉恐惧症的女孩

39:26.281 --> 39:29.455
When this girl came to me, she was so pleased with herself.
这个女孩在找我看病后 对自己很满意

39:29.659 --> 39:31.832
She'd been able to overcome her phobia
她已经能控制她的恐惧

39:31.995 --> 39:36.000
to the extent that she could sit in the same room as a closed banana.
已经可以跟没剥开香蕉坐在一个房间里

39:36.165 --> 39:40.671
It had to stay closed, unzipped, or else she'd go completely psychotic.
原本只要她接近一根剥开的香蕉 她就会完全疯掉

39:40.837 --> 39:44.387
But the point is, open or closed, she had not made the connection
问题是 无论怎样 她从未把

39:44.591 --> 39:46.639
between her phobia and her fear.
自己害怕的东西和恐惧症联系在一起

39:47.552 --> 39:50.556
- Of bananas?  - No. It was something else.
- 就因为香蕉吗?  - 不 是其他的东西

39:50.763 --> 39:54.017
A past trauma. Something more threatening than a mere banana.
是过去的创伤 是比一根香蕉更恐怖的事情

39:54.225 --> 39:56.523
Do you understand? It's like a movie screen.
你明白吗? 就好像电影屏幕

39:56.728 --> 39:59.322
She projected her fear onto the banana
她把自己的恐惧转移到香蕉上

39:59.522 --> 40:02.901
because looking directly at her trauma was too terrifying.
因为她无法直接面对那太恐怖的创伤经历

40:03.109 --> 40:04.611
It was a projection.
香蕉只是个投影

40:04.819 --> 40:07.538
- Onto a piece of fruit?  - Exactly.
- 投影到了一种水果上?  - 正是

40:07.739 --> 40:10.868
Her banana's no different to your launderette.
她的香蕉正是你的洗衣房

40:13.536 --> 40:16.585
I also have a recurring nightmare about an eyeball.
我总是反复做一个关于眼球的噩梦

40:18.416 --> 40:21.386
- What sort of eyeball?  - The giant, floating kind.
- 什么样的眼球?  - 巨大的 漂浮的那种

40:21.586 --> 40:24.635
Sort of eye of death, watching me.
那种死亡之眼 死死盯着我

40:24.839 --> 40:28.810
All fears and neurosis can be traced back to our early childhood.
所有的恐惧和神经衰弱都可追溯至幼时

40:29.010 --> 40:34.642
To the first terrifying recognition that we are alone in the world.
因为发现自己在这世上孤身一人 便第一次认识到了恐惧 

40:34.849 --> 40:37.773
When a young child is abandoned, it has no concept of time.
当一个孩子被抛弃 他就没有了时间概念

40:37.977 --> 40:40.321
No understanding that things can get better.
他不相信一切会变好

40:40.521 --> 40:45.778
That there is hope. For a child, Jack, mother equals life.
毫无希望 对孩子来说 杰克 母亲即是生命

40:45.985 --> 40:47.487
Take away the mother
离开了母亲

40:47.695 --> 40:52.292
and the child is literally swallowed by death.
孩子就同被死亡吞噬没有分别

40:54.410 --> 40:56.629
But I didn't die, did I?
但我没死 不是么?

40:56.788 --> 40:59.462
No. You lived...
是的 你活下来...

40:59.666 --> 41:02.260
to experience your own death.
感受着自己的死亡

41:06.965 --> 41:09.559
That's some scary shit, Dr. Friedkin.
那种感觉真是可怕 弗莱德金医生

41:09.759 --> 41:13.138
