这就好了 小甜豆 我很抱歉 杰克 我们得结束治疗了

41:31.948 --> 41:34.497
I don't know how to thank you, Dr. Friedkin.
真不知道该怎么感谢你 弗莱德金医生

41:38.037 --> 41:42.213
Perhaps as a teenager, you were subliminally drawn to that OOO,
或许在少年时期 你下意识地被000机器吸引了吧

41:42.375 --> 41:45.094
because somewhere deep in your subconscious,
在你的潜意识深处

41:45.294 --> 41:48.013
you recognised that you, too, are out of order.
你认识到 自己也出了差错

41:48.214 --> 41:50.216
Broken. You don't work anymore.
坏掉了 不再灵光了

41:50.591 --> 41:53.060
The primary defence mechanisms you relied on
支持你度过童年的

41:53.261 --> 41:56.731
to get you through childhood no longer support you as an adult.
最主要的心理防御机制 无法在你成年后继续成立

41:56.931 --> 41:58.524
I'm sorry.
很抱歉

41:59.058 --> 42:01.652
You're fucked up, Jack. You need therapy.
你有些混乱 杰克 你需要治疗

42:01.853 --> 42:03.901
I haven't got time. I've got a meeting about an hour.
我没有时间了 我一小时后还有一个会面

42:04.105 --> 42:05.982
Return to the scene of the crime
回到犯罪现场

42:06.149 --> 42:09.494
and retrieve those unwashed articles locked in the machine.
然后找出被锁在机器里那些未清洗过的零件

42:09.694 --> 42:12.038
Release your raw, true, inner self.
释放你真实的本我和内心

42:12.405 --> 42:15.784
Begin a new life, free from fear.
开始新的生活 摆脱恐惧

42:16.367 --> 42:18.290
Fear of death.
对死亡的恐惧

42:23.750 --> 42:28.256
The irony is we must all journey through 
讽刺的是我们所有人在到达天堂前

42:28.463 --> 42:30.591
before we can reach our heaven.
都要历经炼狱

42:32.133 --> 42:38.106
Dr. Friedkin, I think it's time I faced my banana.
弗莱德金医生 我觉得是时候去面对我的香蕉了

43:17.345 --> 43:19.973
It's step-up time, yo, motherfucker.
到出发的时候了 混蛋

44:26.831 --> 44:28.833
It's all right, mate. It's all right.
没事的 伙计 我们没事哈

44:29.000 --> 44:31.173
What the fuck?
怎么回事?

44:37.049 --> 44:38.767
Everything all right, sir?
你还好吗 先生?

44:38.968 --> 44:40.936
Yes. Yes, I'm fine, thank you.
是的 我还好 谢谢

44:41.137 --> 44:45.108
- Looks like you're in a hurry.  - Yes, well, I have an appointment.
- 您看起来很急啊  - 是的 我有一个约会

44:50.062 --> 44:52.190
With death.
和死神

44:53.316 --> 44:56.741
- Excuse me?  - I mean, with the launderette.
- 您说什么?  - 我是说 和洗衣店

44:56.944 --> 44:59.663
I'm going to wash some socks.
我要去洗袜子

44:59.864 --> 45:03.118
- There's no crime in that, is there?  - Not that I'm aware of.
- 洗衣店里没有什么犯罪吧?  - 据我所知没有

45:03.284 --> 45:06.208
Good. Well, I'll be on my way, then. Good night.
很好 那我就走了 晚安

45:06.370 --> 45:08.043
Good night.
晚安

45:17.340 --> 45:19.559
Keep it together, keep it together.
勇敢点 勇敢点

45:19.717 --> 45:23.563
It's only a banana. It's not him you're afraid of, it's only...
就是一个香蕉嘛 你怕的不是他 只是个...

45:28.351 --> 45:31.104
Okay. Stick to the plan.
好吧 保持原计划

45:31.270 --> 45:33.864
If I move fast, I can get in and out in half an hour.
如果我动作快 进去半小时就能出来

45:34.023 --> 45:36.867
That leaves 20 minutes to change and get a taxi north.
剩下二十分钟用来换衣服 叫出租车向北走

45:37.026 --> 45:38.824
No room for error.
绝不能出差错

45:45.826 --> 45:50.707
"Everything automatic. One, open the door."
"一切都是自动的 第一步 打开门"

45:50.915 --> 45:53.088
"Two, get the clothes in."
"第二步 把衣服放进去"

45:53.292 --> 45:57.547
"Three, shut the door and have two pound coins ready."
"第三步 关上门 准备好两英镑硬币"

45:57.755 --> 46:00.850
"Four, place the money in the slot."
"四 把钱放入投币口"

46:01.050 --> 46:03.599
"Five, push your slot in."
"五 按下按钮"

46:13.187 --> 46:14.564
Great.
太好了

46:15.690 --> 46:17.442
How do I manage it?
我该怎么控制恐惧?

46:17.650 --> 46:21.530
I've managed to create a bad impression. I'm still in the street.
我已经有了不妙的感觉 可我还在大街上呢

46:22.238 --> 46:26.368
Okay. Okay, you can do this. You can do this.
好了好了 你能做到的 你能做到

46:57.398 --> 46:59.446
Looks like my lucky day.
看来今天是我幸运日

46:59.608 --> 47:03.454
Only four people and no visible infants.
只有四个人 也没看见婴儿

47:03.612 --> 47:05.410
There, look.
在那 快看

47:05.614 --> 47:08.993
The atmosphere's easing a little. I'm blending in.
气氛已经有所缓和 我要进去了

47:17.376 --> 47:21.506
Okay, so far so good. I'm already up to number three.
好的 目前为止都不错 我该进行第三步了

47:22.089 --> 47:24.842
"Shut the door, have two pound coins ready."
"关好门 准备好两镑硬币"

47:29.221 --> 47:32.020
"Four, put the money in. Five..."
"四 把钱放进去 五..."

47:35.686 --> 47:38.565
Shit. These signs are older than the machines.
该死 这些标志比机器还要旧

47:38.773 --> 47:40.525
What do I do now?
我现在该怎么办?

47:40.900 --> 47:42.368
Heavy soil.
选重度污渍

47:46.405 --> 47:49.158
Jesus, it's over.
天啊 终于弄好了

47:49.325 --> 47:53.580
All I have to do is stand in front of it until the things come out clean.
我现在要做的就是站在它前面直到它们全部变干净

48:12.765 --> 48:15.814
I need to check out those drying machines.
我得去看看那些烘干机

48:19.980 --> 48:23.826
Interesting. It appears the technique is to open the door
有意思 看起来技巧就是在干衣服飞过的时候

48:24.026 --> 48:26.370
and grab the dry things as they fly past.
快速打开门把它们拽出来

48:26.570 --> 48:30.575
So more heat gets concentrated into bulkier items such as woollens.
烘干的热量就可以更集中于大件 比如毛料衣服

48:30.741 --> 48:32.960
While at the same time anything fragile
同时还可以避免

48:33.119 --> 48:35.292
are spared unnecessary exposure.
小件的衣服不会暴露

48:35.621 --> 48:37.794
I'll have to remember that for my shirt.
我要注意 我的衬衫也要这么办

48:37.998 --> 48:39.545
Wait.
等等

48:40.668 --> 48:42.136
Something's wrong.
不太对劲

48:42.336 --> 48:46.591
I'm spinning without a problem, but mine's different to the others.
我的操作程序没有错 为什么我的看起来跟其他人的不一样

48:46.799 --> 48:48.972
What is this? I can't afford a hitch.
什么情况? 我不能接受

48:49.176 --> 48:50.723
Excuse me.
请问

48:50.928 --> 48:53.602
- Mine hasn't gone white yet.  - What hasn't?
- 我的还没有变白  - 什么没变白?

48:53.806 --> 48:56.025
My washing water. Look.
洗衣服的水 看

48:59.395 --> 49:01.318
You didn't put no soap in.
你没放洗衣粉

49:01.522 --> 49:05.823
- I thought the machine did it.  - Machine don't put own soap in.
- 我以为机器会自动放的  - 机器不会自动放洗衣粉

49:06.026 --> 49:08.370
You have to put soap in. Where your soap?
你得自己放 你的洗衣粉呢?

49:08.571 --> 49:11.575
I haven't got any. It says everything's automatic.
我没有啊 这不是说全自动吗

49:11.782 --> 49:15.252
See number six, "Add detergent."
看第六条 "添加洗涤剂"

49:16.370 --> 49:17.963
No.
哦不

49:18.789 --> 49:20.507
What am I gonna do?
那我该怎么办?

49:20.708 --> 49:25.509
- It's not gonna get washed, is it?  - Not without soap.
- 这样是洗不干净的 对吧?  - 不放洗衣粉的话 是的

49:26.672 --> 49:29.266
I've done it again. How is it possible
我又搞砸了 怎么可能

49:29.425 --> 49:32.429
to keep putting things into machines without getting them clean?
脏衣服放到机器里 却无法得到干净衣服

49:32.595 --> 49:34.939
Look here. Have you got any soap?
请问 你有洗衣粉吗?

49:35.139 --> 49:38.063
Soap in slot machine one pound.
自动洗衣粉机 一镑一盒

49:46.025 --> 49:47.743
Here, soap.
给 洗衣粉

49:48.110 --> 49:49.703
Thanks.
谢谢

49:53.282 --> 49:55.250
Not now.
现在别放

49:55.451 --> 49:58.796
You cannot put soap in now, you've missed your cycle.
现在不能放洗衣粉 已经错过了

49:58.996 --> 50:00.373
You wait.
你得等着

50:00.581 --> 50:03.926
- Tell me when to put the soap.  - No. I'm in hurry to go home.
- 要放的时候告诉我一下  - 没空 我要回家

50:04.126 --> 50:05.799
So am I.
我也是

50:05.961 --> 50:08.965
You haven't been here since 8:00 this morning.
你可不像我 早上八点就来了

50:09.507 --> 50:11.555
What've you got in there?
你都洗了些什么?

50:12.801 --> 50:15.145
- A shirt and some socks.  - That's it?
- 一件衬衫还有些袜子  - 就这些?

50:15.804 --> 50:17.477
No.
不是

50:18.807 --> 50:21.856
- There's a pair in there as well.  - A pair?
- 还有条底裤  - 一条?

50:22.061 --> 50:23.734
A pair of underpants?
一条内裤?

50:24.104 --> 50:27.654
- That's all you put in machine?  - I'm allowed to, aren't I?
- 你就放了这点东西进去?  - 怎么了 不可以吗?

50:27.816 --> 50:30.194
You can put in a handkerchief for all I care.
你只放个手绢进去我也没意见

50:30.361 --> 50:33.080
But I think it's a criminal waste of water.
但浪费水简直是太可怕了

50:33.239 --> 50:36.539
Sorry. How right you are.
对不起 你说的对

50:36.700 --> 50:40.295
In fact in a funny way, crime is the only reason I'm here.
搞笑点来说 正是由于害怕我才来这里

50:40.496 --> 50:42.840
I'm going home. It's half past seven.
我要回家了 都七点半了

50:43.040 --> 50:45.793
Actually it's 7:20. But if I'd been in here
实际上才七点二十 但是如果

50:46.001 --> 50:49.881
since 8:00, I'd have started lying about more than the time to get out.
我是早上八点就来了 我也愿意把回家的时间说的紧迫点

50:54.051 --> 50:57.396
- We'll miss out the drying.  - Yeah, I agree.
- 好像已经烘干了  - 应该是

51:07.815 --> 51:09.567
I've missed my cycle.
我错过了放洗衣粉的时机

51:09.775 --> 51:11.448
Will it still get clean?
还能洗干净吗?

51:11.652 --> 51:14.656
I'm gonna have to chance it. I'm cutting it fine as it is.
冒险试试看吧 也许凑合能洗干净

51:14.863 --> 51:17.707
And why do I seem to be the only one with a machine
但是为什么只有我的这个洗衣机

51:17.908 --> 51:20.252
that refuses to stop spinning?
一直没完没了地转呢?

51:28.252 --> 51:30.630
Those two are beginning to annoy me.
这两个人让我很困扰

51:30.838 --> 51:34.809
Especially the one in the rollers who looks like Caligula.
尤其是那个重金属版的卡里古拉大帝（罗马的一位暴君）

51:35.009 --> 51:37.262
She's obviously the ring leader.
她肯定是个帮派头目

51:39.471 --> 51:41.849
What the hell are they staring at?
见鬼 他们盯着看什么呢?

51:42.057 --> 51:44.731
I imagine they live pretty mundane lives here
我想她们在这洗衣房里过着

51:44.935 --> 51:47.404
in these launderettes, but even so...
平庸的生活 但即使如此...

51:47.938 --> 51:51.613
It's over. I'm free. Get me out of here.
洗好了 我自由了 我解放了

52:19.803 --> 52:21.805
Oh, no. A beautiful girl.
哦 不 来了个美女（长得跟MJ似的还美女)

52:22.014 --> 52:23.857
That's the last thing I need.
这是我最不想见到的

52:24.016 --> 52:26.769
It's bad enough shifting underwear with these louts.
对着这些俗人把内裤搬来搬去的就够糟了

52:26.935 --> 52:29.404
Now I'm gonna have to do it with her watching.
现在还得当着美女的面这么做

52:30.898 --> 52:34.493
Better be discrete, it's down to the dryers now.
还好没缠一起 现在走向烘干机

52:46.997 --> 52:48.624
I'll just hang back here.
就待在这儿

52:48.791 --> 52:51.465
Hope the beautiful girl doesn't notice my presence.
希望美女别注意到我

52:54.630 --> 52:56.883
She's trying to block my view of her dryer.
她试图挡住我的视线

52:57.091 --> 52:59.594
What does she think I am? A Peeping Tom?
她以为我是什么人? 偷窥狂吗?

53:00.469 --> 53:04.895
Jesus. The size of that. I've never seen anything like it.
上帝啊 瞧那尺寸 没见过这么大的

53:05.432 --> 53:09.278
And another. That thing must have "Dunlop" written on it.
还有一个 这是邓禄普牌的吗?(轮胎品牌)

53:09.478 --> 53:12.823
Oh, thanks. Thanks very much.
行 谢啦 非常感谢

53:12.981 --> 53:15.109
That's just downright impolite.
原谅我的失礼

53:15.275 --> 53:18.654
Listen, darling, I don't wanna look at your fucking underwear.
听着 亲爱的 我不想看你的破内衣

53:18.821 --> 53:22.451
It might excite the gentlemen in your life, but as far as I'm concerned
可能有男人会对那感兴趣 但是对我来说

53:22.658 --> 53:26.538
it's about as sexy as a couple of buckets, which is what it looks like.
那就像俩吊桶一样性感 根本就是两个吊桶

53:37.881 --> 53:40.304
I look like something out of a horror movie.
我看起来像恐怖片里的怪物

53:40.467 --> 53:42.561
All those little ruptured blonde hairs.
我那美丽的金色秀发啊

53:42.761 --> 53:45.640
My head looks like a Swede's scrotum.
我脑袋看起来像个瑞典大阴囊

53:45.848 --> 53:50.149
No wonder they've been watching me. I look horrifying.
难怪他们都看着我 我看起来真恐怖

53:50.352 --> 53:52.400
I'm a monster.
我是个怪物

53:55.274 --> 53:56.901
What to do?
怎么办?

53:59.653 --> 54:01.747
I've still got half an hour.
还有半个小时

54:02.030 --> 54:06.410
I could go to the service station, get some big sunglasses.
我可以去商店 买个大墨镜

54:06.618 --> 54:09.292
Yeah. Yeah.
对 很好

54:09.496 --> 54:10.998
Yeah, it could work.
对 就这么办

54:11.206 --> 54:14.130
Yeah, motherfucker. Hood up.
很好 操他妈的 还有兜帽

54:14.334 --> 54:18.464
Right, I've gotta get out of here. And quick.
行了 我得离开这 尽快

54:18.964 --> 54:21.467
A bit of dampness never hurt anybody.
潮一点没关系的

54:52.623 --> 54:55.251
Forget them. They're lost forever.
忘了它吧 它一去不返了

54:55.459 --> 54:57.553
Just get the sock and the shirt.
赶紧拿袜子和衬衫

55:00.506 --> 55:02.304
Excuse me.
不好意思

55:03.467 --> 55:04.844
Are these yours?
这是你的吗?

55:07.221 --> 55:08.689
No.
不是

55:08.889 --> 55:10.516
No. Nothing to do with me.
跟我没关系

55:14.144 --> 55:17.523
- Are they yours?  - They're his. I saw them come out.
- 是你们的吗?  - 就是他的 我看到了

55:19.983 --> 55:22.702
- Excuse me. What's your name?  - John.
- 请问 你叫什么名字?  - 约翰

55:22.903 --> 55:25.497
- My name is John.  - Then they are yours.
- 我叫约翰  - 那这就是你的

55:25.697 --> 55:28.701
It's embroidered inside on a little tab.
里面标签上有你的名字

55:30.118 --> 55:32.667
Yes. Yes, they are. They are mine, yes.
是 没错 是我的 是我的

55:32.871 --> 55:34.794
Lent them to somebody, long time ago.
借给别人了 好久以前

55:34.998 --> 55:37.342
Not sure how they got into my wash actually.
不知道怎么又跑到洗衣机里去了

55:37.793 --> 55:39.841
- Don't you want them?  - No.
- 你不要了?  - 不要了

55:40.045 --> 55:41.888
No. No, thank you.
不要了 谢谢

55:42.381 --> 55:45.180
- I don't want them.  - Throw them in the bin, love.
- 我也不要啊  - 扔垃圾桶吧 亲爱的

55:45.384 --> 55:47.682
Yes, thank you. You've been very kind.
好的 谢谢 麻烦你啦

55:47.886 --> 55:49.513
Look out. He's got a blade.
小心 他有刀

55:52.432 --> 55:56.232
It's not what it looks like. I'm not gonna hurt anybody. Really.
不是你们想的那样 我不会伤害任何人的 真的

55:56.395 --> 55:59.490
I'm a professional writer. For television. Don't go.
我是职业作家 写电视剧的 别跑啊

55:59.815 --> 56:01.237
- Call the cops!  - Please.
- 报警!  - 不要

56:01.400 --> 56:04.620
- Call the cops!  - No, no. Stop, stop, stop.
- 报警  - 不要 别 别

56:05.571 --> 56:07.198
Argh!
啊!

56:08.198 --> 56:10.576
- Go.  - Get.
- 快跑  - 快

56:10.742 --> 56:13.120
Where's the cops?
警察呢?

56:16.832 --> 56:19.676
Go that way. Take that route, gotta get that next one.
走那边 从那条路 下个路口看看

56:34.516 --> 56:36.234
Half past.
半点过了

56:37.144 --> 56:39.238
I've still got 20 minutes.
还有二十分钟

56:46.945 --> 56:49.414
- Back off.  - Please, I can explain.
- 退后  - 求你了 让我解释一下

56:49.615 --> 56:52.835
- Let me out. I can explain.  - No way. Go on, stay back.
- 让我出去 我可以解释  - 别想 继续 退后

56:53.035 --> 56:58.132
Look, I know I look weird, but I'm a writer.
听着 我知道看起来很怪 我是个作家

56:58.290 --> 56:59.963
I don't normally look like this
平时我不是这样的

57:00.125 --> 57:02.344
and I certainly don't wanna use this knife.
我真的没打算用刀子

57:02.544 --> 57:04.922
Please, I have a really important meeting.
求你了 我有个很重要的约会

57:05.130 --> 57:08.760
Not interested, mate, okay? And I said back off.
